STATE of North Carolina
v.
Donald Wayne MIMS. No. 173P05. Supreme Court of North Carolina. May 4, 2005. Donald Wayne Mims, Pro Se. William P. Hart, Special Deputy Attorney General, C. Colon Willoughby, Jr., District Attorney, for State of NC.

ORDER

Upon consideration of the petition filed by Defendant on the 30th day of March 2005 in this matter for a writ of certiorari to review the order of the Superior Court, Wake County, the following order was entered and is hereby certified to the Superior Court of that County:

"Dismissed by order of the Court in conference, this the 4th day of May 2005."
